The treatment of thoracic and lumbar spine fractures: a study of 123 cases treated surgically in 101 patients. For a total of 123 thoracolumbar traumatic lesions treated surgically in 101 patients over approximately 2 years (all monitored clinically and radiographically up to consolidation by follow-ups after from 6 to 26 months, mean 10 months) the technique used, complications and treatment are reported. The treatment procedure included: emergency surgery decompression, osteosynthesis, and fusion (posterior and possibly intersomatic) immediate recovery of function and loading